		<pb n="1"/>
          <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Barbados</placeName> <date>23 Nov. 1848</date></p>
          <p><addressee>Revd. Isaac Leeser</addressee> </p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">My Dear Sir</p>
          <p rend="indent(2)">I have this instant heard that there is<lb/> a conveyance for <placeName>Baltimore</placeName>&#44; and embrace the opportunity<lb/> reluctantly to inform you that the set of Parasah Books<lb/> you sent me in the early part of last year&#44; I had sold<lb/> to the <persName>Revd. John Birchannon</persName><add>&#63;</add> of the <add>&#63;</add> of Barbie with<lb/> a promise that the amount would be remitted me shortly<lb/> after his arrival&#44; but <del>but</del> by the last steamer&#44; I received<lb/> a letter announcing his death&#44; and that all his property had<lb/> been levied on by excusion to pay a prior claim against him&#44; con&#45;<lb/>&#45;sequently the amount he is indebted to me is lost&#44; as he<lb/> has nothing else available to pay&#44; however on my arrival<lb/> please God&#44; I hope we shall be able to understand each other&#44;<lb/> as it is not likely we&#39;ll fight about such a trifle as fifteen<lb/> dollars&#8212;please present my family&#39;s line to my sister&#44; <persName>Mr.<lb/> Fontes</persName> and the <persName>Carvalhos</persName>&#44; and say my wife is busily em&#45;<lb/>&#45;ployed cutting out flannels&#44; and other warm clothing in<lb/> readiness for our departure&#44; and as I have to attend in pur&#45;<lb/>&#45;chasing the different articles&#44; I have no time to write<lb/> either of them&#44; hoping that on my arrival please God<lb/> a mutual good understanding will exist between us&#44; and<lb/> that it may be in our power to assist each other.</p>
          <p rend="indent(10)">I remain</p>
          <p rend="indent(10)">My Dear Sir</p>
          <p rend="indent(10)">Your&#39;s faithfully</p>
          <p rend="indent(10)"><persName role="author">Samuel E. Daniels</persName></p>
